{
  "id": "q-passkey-smart-account-architecture",
  "question": "How do passkey smart wallets work on Stellar: what does __check_auth do, what does native secp256r1 provide, and what is shared versus per user?",
  "surface": [
    "stellarDocs.search_wallet_dapp_docs",
    "skills.stellar-dev.dapp",
    "skills.stellar-dev.smart-contracts"
  ],
  "golden": {
    "answer": "A Stellar smart wallet is a contract account whose reserved __check_auth validates credentials and policy for the Soroban authorization context. CAP-0051 added native secp256r1/P-256 verification in Protocol 21, but that primitive alone is not complete WebAuthn validation: wallet code must bind the challenge to the Soroban authorization payload and validate client/authenticator data, RP ID/origin, and required presence or verification flags. Store the P-256 public key and, when needed, credential ID plus policy/recovery state; the private key remains in the authenticator/provider. Per-user instances commonly share one Wasm hash; an external shared verifier or policy contract is optional.",
    "keyFacts": [
      "A contract account implements __check_auth to validate credentials and authorization policy.",
      "CAP-0051 added native secp256r1/P-256 verification in Protocol 21, but P-256 verification alone is not complete WebAuthn validation.",
      "WebAuthn handling binds the challenge to the Soroban authorization payload and validates client/authenticator data, RP ID/origin, and required flags.",
      "Store public credential and policy/recovery state on-chain as needed; the private passkey key remains in the authenticator/provider.",
      "Per-user instances may share a Wasm hash; a shared external verifier/policy contract is optional, not required."
    ],
    "avoid": [
      "A raw valid P-256 signature is complete WebAuthn assertion validation.",
      "The private passkey key should be stored on-chain.",
      "All users of a shared wallet Wasm hash share one contract account and balance."
    ],
    "notes": "Status-sensitive details are stated as of 2026-07-11; grade later sourced changes leniently and require dated primary evidence."
  },
